CyclePresenter
public class LazyPresenter<V extends LazyView,E extends EventBus>
extends BasePresenter<V,E>

Special type of presenter that will be built only when it handles its first event. To do so, the bind method (that is called only the first time a presenter needs to handle an event) is divided in two:

  • createPresenter: method where presenter should be built (ie all its attributes should be instantiated). By default, it does nothing.
  • bindView: method where required bindings between this Presenter and its View should be done. By default it does nothing.
A LazyPresenter can only have a view which type is compatible with LazyView. This type of presenter will automatically call the createView method of the LazyView when its bind method is called.

Author:
plcoirier
